00:14:47,388 --> 00:14:48,609
so I apologize for the awkwardness.

311
00:14:48,789 --> 00:14:50,471
But a lot of people have asked me how to navigate

312
00:14:50,511 --> 00:14:52,672
sort of exclusivity and multi-platform launches.

313
00:14:52,692 --> 00:14:54,613
And this is probably a good rough guide

314
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:56,915
of the sort of support that you'll get,

315
00:14:56,955 --> 00:14:58,596
and it's basically the same for each platform.

316
00:14:58,997 --> 00:15:00,578
But essentially, if you self-publish

317
00:15:00,618 --> 00:15:02,079
with some exclusivity on a platform,

318
00:15:02,099 --> 00:15:04,080
you're likely going to get some degree of the support

319
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:06,282
from the platform, and that's your best chance of doing so

320
00:15:07,202 --> 00:15:08,403
if you put the game everywhere,

321
00:15:09,324 --> 00:15:10,665
like you can see on the bottom.

322
00:15:11,765 --> 00:15:14,647
Maybe not as much, or actually the fourth line, I guess.

323
00:15:16,487 --> 00:15:19,929
And if you work with a publisher, then it really depends on that publisher's relationship with the platform.

324
00:15:20,969 --> 00:15:25,011
But coming out second on a platform, again, doesn't mean that they're not going to give you any support.

325
00:15:25,031 --> 00:15:26,612
It just means you need to find your champion there.

326
00:15:30,152 --> 00:15:33,654
I've said in the past, you only get one launch, so you should nail it.

327
00:15:35,274 --> 00:15:39,056
But also, that's not true when you get lots of launches across every platform over multiple

328
00:15:39,076 --> 00:15:39,436
years.

329
00:15:40,497 --> 00:15:43,438
And if you do do that, then you're going to need the best champion you can find for all

330
00:15:43,478 --> 00:15:43,719
of them.

331
00:15:45,399 --> 00:15:48,121
You can have multiple champions, and you should have multiple champions.

332
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:51,332
Platforms largely understand that you need to make

333
00:15:51,352 --> 00:15:53,053
the most sustainable decisions for your business

334
00:15:53,193 --> 00:15:55,034
and that you should take the best deals offered.

335
00:15:55,114 --> 00:15:55,975
And there were lots of occasions

336
00:15:55,995 --> 00:15:56,896
where I would tell a developer

337
00:15:56,916 --> 00:15:58,617
to go take a deal from someone else.

338
00:15:59,618 --> 00:16:01,119
And if someone was bitter about that,

339
00:16:01,379 --> 00:16:03,181
I think you probably shouldn't be working with them anyways.

340
00:16:05,903 --> 00:16:07,784
So weird that they gave us milk to drink for this.

