00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:16,231
So let's go through the steps of this,

343
00:16:16,311 --> 00:16:18,112
of how to find and maximize your champion.

344
00:16:20,287 --> 00:16:22,408
What does this mean, making the right game?

345
00:16:22,688 --> 00:16:24,429
Step one, can you make the wrong game?

346
00:16:24,689 --> 00:16:26,950
And I don't like that idea, I don't like how it sounds

347
00:16:27,010 --> 00:16:28,871
because I believe that games are art first

348
00:16:28,911 --> 00:16:30,993
and products second, and I really want you

349
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:32,413
to make the game that you wanna make.

350
00:16:32,814 --> 00:16:34,815
However, it's still good to understand what you're making

351
00:16:34,895 --> 00:16:36,896
and its implications on your potential champion.

352
00:16:39,457 --> 00:16:41,118
And this could be a whole separate talk,

353
00:16:41,138 --> 00:16:42,539
but we're just gonna cover the basics of it.

354
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,760
So I think really the easiest types of games

355
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:47,802
to get excited about generally.

356
00:16:48,756 --> 00:16:51,838
are games that are either doing something fundamentally new.

357
00:16:52,478 --> 00:16:54,540
So these, you know, these games are getting older at this point,

358
00:16:55,261 --> 00:17:00,084
but I'd say all of these that are you are doing something fundamentally new in games and not just in their genres.

359
00:17:00,985 --> 00:17:03,247
Or you could do something that's sort of the best of a genre.

360
00:17:03,787 --> 00:17:07,990
Here's some other examples of things that are maybe not radically new, but did what they did really well.

361
00:17:08,977 --> 00:17:12,240
And if you're not doing one or the other of these things, you're going to have a much tougher time.

362
00:17:13,462 --> 00:17:16,905
And it's less likely, probably, that you're going to make something that's the best of a genre,

363
00:17:16,945 --> 00:17:20,289
just because that's a lot tougher, but you can definitely make something new, or you can try to make something new.

364
00:17:21,830 --> 00:17:28,016
And I'd also say that the one thing to me that all these games have in common is either great art, or at least memorable art.

365
00:17:28,056 --> 00:17:29,198
So visuals really do matter.

366
00:17:30,979 --> 00:17:34,180
And this past Saturday I was hanging out with my friend Zach Gage, and he said something

367
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:38,222
else that I really liked about what sorts of games might have the best chances of success

368
00:17:38,282 --> 00:17:38,602
right now.

369
00:17:39,623 --> 00:17:42,764
And then last night I was up pretty late and I started Googling pictures of Zach to add

370
00:17:42,784 --> 00:17:46,726
to this talk, and he's just such an impossible dreamboat.

